    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 21,
    "last_activity_date" : 1249030607,
    "creation_date" : 1249030607,
    "answer_id" : 1211408,
    "question_id" : 291003,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>There is in fact a functional change: <code>org.junit.Assert</code> will complain if you use the two-argument <code>assertEquals()</code> with <code>float</code> or <code>double</code>, while <code>junit.framework.Assert</code> will silently autobox it.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
