    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In Android Studio (and so in IntelliJ too), you can globally exclude <code>junit.framework</code> from auto-import proposal.</p>\n\n<p>You can set the scope between <code>IDE</code> or <code>Project</code>. If you don't have projects which use JUnit 3 you can safely stay with IDE scope.</p>\n\n<p>Setting position: </p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Preferences -> Editor -> General -> Auto Import</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/MYacE.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/MYacE.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n"
  } ],
